# Project Structure

This full-stack inventory and invoicing application is organized with separate frontend and backend directories:

## Frontend Structure
- Entry point: [frontend/src/main.jsx](mdc:frontend/src/main.jsx)
- Main application component: [frontend/src/App.jsx](mdc:frontend/src/App.jsx)
- Key directories:
  - `frontend/src/components/` - Reusable UI components
  - `frontend/src/pages/` - Page-level components
  - `frontend/src/contexts/` - React context providers
  - `frontend/src/hooks/` - Custom React hooks
  - `frontend/src/services/` - API services for backend communication
  - `frontend/src/utils/` - Utility functions
  - `frontend/src/styles/` - CSS and styling files
  - `frontend/src/layouts/` - Layout components

## Backend Structure
- Entry point: [backend/server.js](mdc:backend/server.js)
- Key directories:
  - `backend/routes/` - API route definitions
  - `backend/controllers/` - Request handlers
  - `backend/models/` - MongoDB schema models
  - `backend/services/` - Business logic services
  - `backend/middleware/` - Express middleware
  - `backend/utils/` - Utility functions

## Configuration Files
- Frontend:
  - [frontend/package.json](mdc:frontend/package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
  - [frontend/vite.config.js](mdc:frontend/vite.config.js) - Vite configuration
  - [frontend/tailwind.config.js](mdc:frontend/tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind CSS styling
  - [frontend/jsconfig.json](mdc:frontend/jsconfig.json) - JavaScript configuration

- Backend:
  - [backend/package.json](mdc:backend/package.json) - Dependencies and scripts

## Database Seeding
The database can be seeded with initial data using [backend/seed.js](mdc:backend/seed.js).
